Fast systems language, memory safe, good for reliable code, harder to learn at first

Common type sizes:

| Type | Size |
| --- | --- |
| bool | 1 byte |
| u8 / i8 | 1 byte |
| u16 / i16 | 2 bytes |
| u32 / i32 | 4 bytes |
| u64 / i64 | 8 bytes |
| u128 / i128 | 16 bytes |
| usize / isize | 4 bytes on 32-bit systems, 8 bytes on 64-bit systems |
| f32 | 4 bytes |
| f64 | 8 bytes |
| char | 4 bytes |
| pointer/reference | 4 bytes on 32-bit systems, 8 bytes on 64-bit systems |

Array size is element size times length. Struct and enum sizes can include padding and layout overhead.
